---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Jenny K Walsh — Caseworthy">
  <div class="case-study">

    <div class="case-study-header">
      <p class="label">Caseworthy &nbsp;·&nbsp; Work overview</p>
      <h1>Director of UX Design</h1>
      <p class="role">2017 – 2018</p>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-image">
      <img src="/work/caseworthy/hero.webp" alt="Caseworthy" />
    </div>

    <div class="content">

      <section class="intro">
        <p>Caseworthy is a case management platform built for non-profit organizations. As Director of UX/UI Design, I led the first-ever UX overhaul of their core application, redesigning the client management and reporting products, leading a front-end dev team, and building a new sales website from scratch.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Redesigning the core app</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>A significant portion of my time at Caseworthy was dedicated to reshaping the information architecture of their central single-page application. The company had a decade-long history without a dedicated designer. The team had built sturdy, reliable software used by non-profits nationwide, but it had never been designed with a user-centered lens.</p>
          <p>The goal wasn't to start from scratch. It was to make what already existed genuinely easier to use for the people who depended on it: caseworkers and coordinators at non-profits doing real, important work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="image-break image-break--full">
          <img src="/work/caseworthy/ui%20screens.webp" alt="" />
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2>Additional responsibilities</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <p>Beyond product design, I led a team of front-end developers, providing direction and helping bridge the gap between design and implementation. Together we rebuilt the public-facing sales website and created a new suite of marketing materials.</p>
          <p>Bringing design thinking into an engineering-led organization meant a lot of translation work: making the case for user research, establishing design process, and keeping quality high through implementation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="image-break image-break--full">
          <img src="/work/caseworthy/website-refresh.webp" alt="" />
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <div class="content content-lower">

      <section class="section notable">
        <h2>Notable work</h2>
        <div class="section-body">
          <ul class="accomplishments">
            <li>Redesign of the sales &amp; marketing website</li>
            <li>Redesign of the client management system</li>
            <li>Redesign of the reporting product</li>
            <li>Led front-end development team on implementation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="image-break">
        <img src="/work/caseworthy/print-sales-material.webp" alt="" />
      </div>

      <div class="back-link">
        <a href="/work">← All work</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .case-study {
    padding-bottom: 8rem;
    overflow-x: hidden;
  }

  .case-study-header {
    padding: 180px 3rem 3rem;
    max-width: 1200px;
  }

  .label {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--black);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .role {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--white);
    background: var(--black);
    padding: 0.3rem 0.75rem;
  }

  .hero-image {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .hero-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 1200px;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .intro {
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    font-weight: 300;
  }

  .section {
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 280px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.2;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .section-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .image-break {
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
  }

  .image-break img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .image-break--full {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .accomplishments {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .accomplishments li {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .accomplishments li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .notable {
    background: var(--black);
    color: var(--white);
    padding: 4rem 3rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-top: none;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .notable h2 {
    color: #F6FF00;
  }

  .back-link {
    padding: 4rem 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .back-link a {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    text-decoration: none;
    background-color: #F6FF00;
    padding: 0 4px;
    display: inline-block;
    transition: box-shadow 0.1s steps(2), transform 0.1s steps(2);
  }

  .back-link a:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: 4px 2px 0 #00FFFF, -4px -2px 0 #FF00FF;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .case-study-header {
      padding: 160px 1.5rem 2rem;
    }

    .content {
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
    }

    .intro {
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      padding: 2rem 0;
    }

    .back-link {
      padding: 2rem 0 0;
    }

    .content-lower {
      padding-left: 0;
      padding-right: 0;
    }

    .notable {
      padding: 2rem;
      border-radius: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
